# LSP Features — Complete Reference

## Per-Symbol LSP Files

| Virtual file | LSP method | Purpose |
|-|-|-|
| `CALLERS.md` / `callers/` | `callHierarchy/incomingCalls` | Who calls this symbol |
| `DEPS.md` / `deps/` | `callHierarchy/outgoingCalls` | What this symbol calls |
| `REFERENCES.md` / `references/` | `textDocument/references` | All reference sites |
| `DECLARATION.md` / `declaration/` | `textDocument/declaration` | Where declared |
| `DEFINITION.md` / `definition/` | `textDocument/definition` | Where defined |
| `IMPLEMENTATION.md` / `implementation/` | `textDocument/implementation` | Where implemented |
| `TYPE-DEFINITION.md` / `type-definition/` | `textDocument/typeDefinition` | Type definition location |
| `DOC.md` / `hover/` | `textDocument/hover` | Hover documentation |
| `HINTS.md` | `textDocument/inlayHint` | Inlay hints |
| `DIAGNOSTICS.md` | `textDocument/publishDiagnostics` | Errors/warnings |
| `actions/*.diff` | `textDocument/codeAction` | Suggested fixes |
| `rename/new.diff` | `textDocument/rename` | Rename preview |

## File-Level LSP Files

| Virtual file | Aggregation |
|-|-|
| `file.ext@/DIAGNOSTICS.md` | All diagnostics in this file |
| `file.ext@/actions/` | Code actions across the file |

## Symlink Semantics

All symlink directories (`callers/`, `deps/`, `references/`, etc.) point to symbol
directories. The `.ext` shorthand resolves through symlinks:

```
callers/init.{{ ext }} → main.{{ ext }}@/symbols/init@/body.{{ ext }}
deps/validate.{{ ext }} → utils.{{ ext }}@/symbols/validate@/body.{{ ext }}
```

Follow symlinks to traverse the codebase without knowing file paths.

## Markdown vs Symlink Directories

Each relationship has both forms:

- **`CALLERS.md`** — human-readable, includes inline code context, good for one-shot reads
- **`callers/`** — machine-navigable, symlinks for traversal and editing

Use markdown files when reading for understanding. Use symlink directories when
traversing to edit.

## Fallback Behavior

When LSP is unavailable for a language:

- Markdown files return a note indicating LSP is unavailable
- Symlink directories are empty
- `ENOTSUP` on writes that require LSP (e.g., rename)
- Tree-sitter decomposition still works — symbol bodies, signatures, etc. are available
- Only LSP-dependent features (callers, references, rename, diagnostics) are affected
